 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "intro",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# MT metrics vs MQM \n",
    "\n",
    "We use WMT-style data in `wmt_mqm_2023_scored.csv` (en-de). The notebook scores outputs with BLEU, chrF, and optionally COMET, compares to human MQM, and splits segments into dev (80%) and test (20%). Stress slices use entity counts from the CSV plus regex hits on numbers/money/dates in the English source; the cutoff is fit on dev only (matches the proposal idea).\n",
    "\n",
    "No separate training split: we only use dev for tuning the stress threshold and exploration, and test for numbers we treat as held out.\n",
    "\n",
    "Run the pip cell first so installs hit the same kernel Jupyter is using. If COMET is too heavy, set RUN_COMET = False in the next cell.\n",
    "\n",
    "Install from terminal if you prefer: pip install pandas sacrebleu scipy scikit-learn torch unbabel-comet\n",
    "\n",
    "On Mac, COMET may run on CPU only; the code turns off a buggy MPS path.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "724be371",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
